				<div class="postbody">
				Sorry I didn't see myself outed earlier -- I don't come to this forum much, as it's a tad... repetetive, and people aren't debating so much as restating their own opinions ad nauseum.
<br />

<br />
New York City is a place, not an ethnic, racial, religious, or identifiably coloured group of people, so I wouldn't think that "Ih8NYC" would be indictable. Now, if you wore an "Ih8jewsAndYouShouldToo" t-shirt, I'd imagine there'd be cause for some sort of arrest, seizure of said t-shirt, and RCMP jackboots to the genitalia.
<br />

<br />
Yeah, the law looks broad, but so do a majority of laws in every country in the world. An under-two-year sentence is a non-federal offence, and that's the maximum you'd get. I'm sure there's laws in cities all over the world offering to jail you that long for not paying your parking tickets. Hell, isn't %@$#-banditry still illegal in a buncha states?<br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
				</div>
