The laws that actually strike me as stupid are the ones that protect illegal aliens.  Some illegal alien just sued and won here recently when he was admitted for cancer treatment.  He got the treatment but no chemotherapy.  He sued and won for it to the tune of 350,000 dollars.  I don't understand why judges don't simply throw cases out that are similar to this one.  The cases that also get me are when a criminal breaks into a home and then sues the homeowner when the thief breaks his leg when entering the premises.
